Happy new year, happy 2019, thank you 2018 💙

2018 was the year that I got mental breakdown and was the year full of heartbreaks, but also an amazing year ✨ I've gotten stronger because of what I went through.
.
Firstly, I want to apologize because I neglected this fanpage so much in 2018? I was too busy and I had poor time management (which I promise I would fix)
.
I've achieved so much in 2018, so here's 10 of what I am most thankful for 2018:
1) I worked for a while after high school at KFC as cashier
2) Got straight A's for my SPM
3) Bought 2 phones using my own money (huawei and iphone)
4) Got my driving license in a try (both motor and car)
5) Accepted into university 
6) Met new friends 
7) Got out of toxic relationship 
8) Confessed to my 2+ years old crush
9) Got praises and highest carry mark for my public speaking skills 
10) Survive sem 1 .
Also, got my first dUCK 😝
.
I hope in 2019 @wendy.site will grow bigger and I'll be an admin who consistently post updates 💕
.
Thanks for being part of my journey, I love you all cupcakes🥰
.

I don’t condone what Wendy said and how she acted - it was ignorant, insensitive and wrong & I’m definitely disappointed. It’s most definitely not okay to stereotype like this. I hope she will learn, repent and apologise for her actions.

She also never stated that it was white/black people she was imitating. She never said who was popular/cool but she did do an imitation however she never stated if they were black or white at all. It got lost in translation, but I’m not at all saying that what she did was completely justifiable.
But please refrain from leaving unnecessary comments that won’t educate or inform her, it’s understandable that many are angry but it’s not right to leave hate comments that are equally hurtful (that’s stooping so low). Leave the fandom if needed. And don’t come leaving hate comments on a Wendy fanpage, I can’t do anything about what she did.
I’ll be waiting for an apology from Wendy.

Our lovely fans~~~ It’s already been two years since we’ve been together…!! I think time flies so quickly! Right?? Am I the only one that feels like this…?ㅎㅎ Thank you for giving us, Red Velvet, so much love within these two years~ Although we try to pay back that love with good performances and songs, it seems that we always receive more from our fans… Thank you so much, and you all know that I rea~lly like you all and rea~lly love you, right?? As time goes on, I feel like my shyness only continues to grow… heh… heh… I’m… a girl who gets very shy as well… Hmm… I think writing a letter is hard… I’m doing well right now, right?? ㅠㅠ I want my heart to be delivered ㅠㅠ It seems I should return to school… Whenever I read every single letter our fans give to us, I always choke up wondering how you all can say such pretty things… (It’s not a secret that I have to sparate them into groups and read them slowly ♥). They all touch my heart! And remind me that I’m a really happy person… and that I should work even harder~! And I want to see you all even~~ more! ;) ㅎㅎ Writing a letter to someone takes a lot of time, but it’s really hard trying to express your mind and heart as well~ So I’m even more thankful! And! Fans! Have I told you all this before? That you are like family to me~ So even though we can’t spend everyday next to one another…! But through all the letters and cheers left on our official homepage, SNS, and letters, I gain a lot of strength and become even stronger~ I’ve talked too much, haven’t I?? ㅎㅎ Anyway!! Fans!! Thank you so much for two years~ Thank you for being with us! We’ll work even harder to show a better image so please continue to be with us in the future for a lo~ng time!! Although it may be boring because I say it all the time but… really really thank you, and I love you ♥ ♥ ♥ ♥ ♥

Translation; Dear Fans ~ Wendy came here (on the website) to see you guys again! Wait a minute...Let me wipe my tears before i write.

I once again felt how much of a lucky person i am. I'm tearing up because of each and every one of your messages.
Thank you for your big love and interests. And thank you for being Red Velvet's fan. I am here now because you guys exists! Thank you always and again, thank you.
I will work harder to show you a better Wendy, and Red Velvet! I will pay back the love i've received! Love you and love you again!
